definition: *sample form (1: single phase(bulk),2: multi phase (bulk),3: single crystal(bulk) ,4:film,5:film(single))

label: temperature independent term in susceptibility
definition: The static magnetic susceptibility, $\chi(0)$, representing the term in susceptibility that is independent of temperature, often associated with Temperature Independent Paramagnetism (TIP).

label: Curie constant
definition: Curie constant

label: magnetic moment per formula
definition: magnetic moment per formula

label: Curie temperature
definition: Curie temperature

label: Neel temperature
definition: Neel temperature

label: density (gcm-3)
definition: Density

label: hardness at 300 K
definition: A material’s resistance to localized plastic deformation, determined at room temperature (300 kelvin) to assess its mechanical strength in the normal state.

label: Young's modulus at 4.2 K
definition: A measure of a superconducting material’s stiffness or resistance to lengthwise deformation, determined at 4.2 Kelvin to evaluate its elastic behavior in the superconducting state.

label: Young's modulus at 300 K
definition: A material’s stiffness or resistance to stretching or compression, determined at room temperature (300 K) to characterize its elastic properties in the normal (non-superconducting) state.

label: shear modulus at 4.2 K
definition: A measure of a material's rigidity against shear (shape-changing) forces, determined at 4.2 Kelvin to assess its elastic stiffness in the superconducting state.

label: shear modulus at 300 K
definition: A measure of a material's resistance to shear (shape-changing) deformation, determined at room temperature (300 kelvin) to characterize its elastic stiffness in the normal, non-superconducting state.

label: unit of bulk modulus at 4.2 K
unit of bulk modulus at 300 K
Poisson ratio at 4.2 K
definition: A measure of a superconducting material's lateral contraction when stretched longitudinally, determined at 4.2 kelvin to describe its elastic deformation behavior.

label: Poisson ratio at 300 K
definition: A measure of a material’s sideways contraction when stretched lengthwise, determined at room temperature (300 K) to characterize its elastic deformation behavior in the normal (non-superconducting) state.

label: sound velocity at 4.2 K
definition: The speed at which elastic waves propagate through a superconducting material at 4.2 kelvin, reflecting its low-temperature elastic stiffness and lattice dynamics in the superconducting state.

label: sound velocity at 300 K
definition: The speed of elastic waves through a material at room temperature (300 Kelvin), characterizing its elastic stiffness and lattice properties in the normal state.

label: *crystal structure, symmetry
definition: *crystal structure, symmetry ( 1=cubic,2=tetragonal,3=orthorhombic,4=monoclinic,5=triclinic,6=trigonal,7=hexagonal)

label: common name of structure
definition: The conventional or informal name for a material's crystal structure, as commonly used within the condensed matter physics community, particularly as it relates to superconducting materials.

label: space group
definition: space group

label: international table number
definition: The number assigned to a space group, found in the International Tables for Crystallography, which defines the symmetry of a crystal structure.

label: lattice constant a
definition: The crystallographic parameter 'a' defining the length of the unit cell along the 'a' direction.

label: lattice constant b
definition: The length of the unit cell edge along the 'b' direction, which defines the crystal structure geometry in condensed matter materials like superconductors.

label: lattice constant c
definition: The length of the unit cell along the c-axis, critical to the crystal structure in condensed matter physics and superconductivity.

label: *method of analysis for structure
description: *method of analysis for structure (1.X-ray crystallography 2.Neutron　crystallography 3.Powder x-ray diffraction 4.Powder neutron diffraction　5.Electron diffraction）
definition: *method of analysis for structure (1.X-ray crystallography 2.Neutron　crystallography 3.Powder x-ray diffraction 4.Powder neutron diffraction　5.Electron diffraction）

label: temperature dependence of LATA
definition: The variation of the lattice constant 'a' of a crystal structure with changes in temperature.

label: temperature dependence of LATB
definition: The change in the lattice constant along the 'b' direction of a crystal structure with respect to temperature.

label: temperature dependence of LATC
definition: The change in the lattice constant c of a crystal structure with respect to temperature.

label: pressure dependence of LATA
definition: The change in the lattice constant 'a' (a crystallographic dimension) of a material in response to applied external pressure.

label: pressure dependence of LATB
definition: The rate at which the lattice constant 'b' of a crystal structure changes in response to applied external pressure.

label: pressure dependence of LATC
definition: The change in the lattice constant 'c' (one of the unit cell dimensions) of a crystal structure in response to applied pressure.

label: transition temperature (R = 0)
definition: The temperature below which a superconductor exhibits zero electrical resistivity ($R=0$).

label: transition temperature (mid point)
definition: The critical temperature ($T_c$) of a superconductor measured as the temperature at which the electrical resistivity (R) reaches 50% of its normal-state value during the transition to the superconducting state.

label: transition temperature (R = 100%)
definition: The critical temperature ($T_c$) of a superconductor, measured at the onset of superconductivity (where electrical resistivity R = 100%).

label: Tc from susceptibility measurement
definition: The critical temperature (Tc) of a superconductor as determined by the abrupt change in magnetic susceptibility, which signifies the onset of perfect diamagnetism and the superconducting state.

label: lowest temperature for measurement (not superconducting)
definition: The minimum measured temperature for samples that do not exhibit superconductivity.

label: transition width for resistive transition
definition: The temperature range where a superconductor's electrical resistivity drops from 90% to 10% during the transition to the superconducting state.

label: Tc (of this sample) recommended
definition: The recommended superconducting critical temperature ($T_c$) specific to the sample.

label: figure number for Tc(p, x, etc)
description: figure number for Tc(p, x, etc)

label: tc measurement method
description: (1.magnetization, 2.ac susceptibility, 3.resistivity, 4.heat capacity, 5.tunneling, 6.infrared spectroscopy, 7.thermal conductivity, 8.Raman spectroscopy , 9.nuclear magnetic resonance, 10.surface impedance, 11.neutron diffraction, 12.photoemission spectroscopy, 13.microwave transmission, 14.Others)
definition: A technique used to determine the superconducting critical temperature ($T_c$), categorized by methods such as: 1. magnetization, 2. AC susceptibility, 3. resistivity, 4. heat capacity, 5. tunneling, 6. infrared spectroscopy, 7. thermal conductivity, 8. Raman spectroscopy, 9. nuclear magnetic resonance, 10. surface impedance, 11. neutron diffraction, 12. photoemission spectroscopy, 13. microwave transmission, or 14. others.

label: slope at P = 0 in Tc vs P plot
description: slope at P=0 in Tc vs P plot
definition: The initial rate of change of the superconducting transition temperature (Tc) with respect to applied pressure (P) at zero pressure.

label: maximum pressure applied
definition: The highest pressure applied to a sample in an experiment.

label: alpha in Tc = A * M^(-alpha), isotope effect
definition: The exponent $\alpha$ relating the critical temperature ($T_c$) of a superconductor to the isotopic mass ($M$) as $T_c \propto M^{-\alpha}$, defining the magnitude of the isotope effect.

label: isotope element
definition: The element in a superconductor that is isotopically varied to measure the critical temperature change due to the isotope effect.

label: exchange ratio of isotope(%)
definition: The isotope shift coefficient ($\alpha$) quantifying the dependence of the superconducting transition temperature ($T_c$) on the atomic mass ($M$) of the constituent elements, where $T_c \propto M^{-\alpha}$.

label: DTC = Tc - Tc0 for isotope element
definition: The change in superconducting critical temperature due to the presence of an isotope element.

label: volume fraction of Meissner effect(%)
description: volume fraction of Meissner effect, unit=%
definition: volume fraction of Meissner effect, unit=%

definition: Experimental techniques used to determine the gap energy in superconductors, including tunneling, infrared spectroscopy, thermal conductivity, Raman spectroscopy, AC susceptibility, nuclear magnetic resonance, surface impedance, neutron diffraction, ultraviolet photoemission spectroscopy, and microwave transmission.

label: resistivity at 4.2 K for single crystal for J//ab-plane
description: resistivity at 4.2K for single crystal for J//ab plane
definition: Electrical resistivity measured at 4.2 Kelvin for a single-crystal material when the current density (J) flows parallel to the ab-plane of the crystal structure. This value typically represents the residual or normal-state resistivity just above the superconducting transition temperature.

label: resistivity at 4.2 K for single crystal for J//c-axis
description: resistivity at 4.2K for single crystal for J//c-axis
definition: The electrical resistivity of a single crystal, measured at 4.2 K, with the current density (J) directed parallel to the c-axis, used to study fundamental electronic transport properties at cryogenic temperatures.

label: resistivity at 77 K for single crystal for J//ab-plane
description: resistivity at 77K for single crystal for J//ab plane
definition: The electrical resistivity of a single crystal measured at 77 Kelvin, with the current density (J) applied parallel to the crystal's ab-plane.

label: resistivity at 77 K for single crystal for J//c-axis
description: resistivity at 77K for single crystal for J//c-axis
definition: Electrical resistivity of a single crystal at 77 K (liquid nitrogen temperature), measured with the current density (J) parallel to the crystallographic c-axis.

label: resistivity at normal-T for poly crystal
description: resistivity at normal-T for poly crystal
definition: resistivity at normal-T for poly crystal

label: resistivity at normal-T for single crystal for J//ab-plane
description: resistivity at normal-T for single crystal for J//ab plane
definition: Electrical resistivity of a single crystal superconductor measured in the normal state (above $T_c$), with the current density (J) directed parallel to the crystallographic $ab$-plane.

label: resistivity at normal-T for single crystal for J//c-axis
description: resistivity at normal-T for single crystal for J//c-axis
definition: Electrical resistivity of a single crystal above its critical temperature, measured with current density parallel to the c-axis.

label: normal temperature
definition: The temperature, typically room temperature, at which a material is in its normal state and does not exhibit superconductivity.

label: resistivity at RT for poly crystal

definition: resistivity at RT for poly crystal

label: resistivity at RT for single crystal for J//ab-plane
description: resistivity at RT for single crystal for J//ab plane

label: resistivity at RT for single crystal for J//c-axis
description: resistivity at RT for single crystal for J//c-axis
definition: Electrical resistivity measured in a single crystal at room temperature (RT) with the current density (J) directed parallel to the crystallographic c-axis.

label: Hall coefficient at 300 K for single, H//c-axis
description: Hall coefficient at 300K for single, H//c-axis

label: Hall coefficient at 300 K for single, H//ab-plane
description: Hall coefficient at 300K for single, H//ab-plane
definition: The measure of how free charge carriers in a single-crystal material respond to a magnetic field applied parallel to the ab-plane, specifically measured at 300 K.

label: Hall coefficient for single, H//c-axis
definition: The Hall coefficient specifically measured in a single crystal material where the applied magnetic field (H) is oriented parallel to the crystallographic c-axis, quantifying the response of free charge carriers to the magnetic field in this configuration.

label: substrate
definition: The foundational material onto which a superconducting thin film is grown or deposited.

label: target material
